Radio presenter and TV personality Lerato Kganyago seems to be very busy collecting titles this year. Just over a week ago Lerato announced that she was officially married to businessman, Thami Ndlela and she has now announced that she has launched her own range of sanitary pads. Lerato took to her social media accounts to announce that she has been working on this project for months and she can't wait for everything to settle down, so we can meet the brand. "Been working on this baby for months (Self funded)! Can’t wait for everything to settle down, so you can all meet!!!" she captioned the photo. Kganyago also announced that she will be giving the first batch of sanitary pads will go to rural areas for free. 